///////////////////////////////////////////////////////
// Sample off device test app
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////
mycloudsdk_external.py

Description:
This test app is a python script that  demonstrates the following functionality:
 - get auth0 information for a user
 - get user information
 - get device information
 - access device associated with the user account
 - create folder and files on the device
 - read content and metadata of file on device
 - delete file on device

Prerequisite:
Must have a valid mycloud user account and an associated mycloud device.

Usage:
>python mycloudsdk_external.py

Before running the script please add mycloud user account details listed here to the script.
MYCLOUD_TEST_USER_NAME = '<username>'
MYCLOUD_TEST_PASSWORD = '<password>'
MYCLOUD_TEST_CLIENT_ID = '<client_id>'
MYCLOUD_TEST_CLIENT_SECRET = '<client_secret>'


///////////////////////////////////////////////////////
// App Install script for ondevice app
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////
Description:
This is a python script that demonstrates the following functionality:
 - install the ondevice android app on MyCloud device
 - uninstall the ondevice android app from MyCloud device

Prerequisite:
Must have a valid mycloud user account and an associated mycloud device.
Make sure the MyCloud device is on the same network as the computer running the installation script.
Update the install_script.py with your MyCloud account details.

Usage:
>python install_script.py
